The optimistic UI update (lines 90-93) stays exactly the same — it updates the local state before the RPC fires. The rollback on catch stays the same too. Only the RPC call changes from N individual calls to one batch call.

Important: The `toolNames` Set construction on line 91 (`const toolNames = new Set(groupTools.map(t => t.name))`) is used for the optimistic update filter and should stay as-is. The new `toolNames` array for the RPC is a separate variable — use a different name or extract it differently to avoid shadowing. For example:

```ts
const handleToggleGroup = (groupTools: WireToolDef[], checked: boolean) => {
  const myVersion = ++toggleCounter.current;
  const groupToolNames = new Set(groupTools.map(t => t.name));
  updatePluginTools(prev => {
    preToggleRef.current = prev;
    return prev.map(t => (groupToolNames.has(t.name) ? { ...t, enabled: checked } : t));
  });
  void setToolsEnabled(plugin.name, groupTools.map(t => t.name), checked).catch(() => {
    if (toggleCounter.current === myVersion) {
      updatePluginTools(() => preToggleRef.current);
    }
    showToggleError('Failed to toggle group');
  });
};
```
